    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1885-07-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1885-07-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="220" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">No. 220.</seg>
                </opener>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Holguin</persName> and Mr.
                                    <persName>Becerra</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1885-07-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 31,
                                1885</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The speedy pacification of Colombia, which the recovery of Barranquilla
                            presages, is hailed with satisfaction.</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * *</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>T. F. BAYARD.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
